items.sentence: You don\'t have to take your umbrella with you.
You don\'t take anything with you when you die.
You have something in your pockets, don\'t you?
I don\'t know why Tom had to go back to Boston.
I don\'t like it when you talk to me like that.
I don\'t play the bassoon as much as I used to.
I don\'t really know very much about computers.
I don\'t really like going to school very much.
I don\'t think I can do this without your help.
Tom isn\'t going to be angry if Mary does that.
